</p>
<p>Eventually, this will do <em>all</em> the dirty work of markdown parsing and caching. But for now...
keep it simple and <code>return strtoupper($str)</code>. But use your imagination - pretend
like it totally <em>is</em> awesome and is parsing our markdown. In fact, it's so awesome
that we want to use it in our controller. How?</p>
<p>Find <code>GenusController</code>. First, create a new object with <code>$transformer = new MarkdownTransformer()</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="a6d14358cf">
